"title": "2030: Jesus Christ, holiness of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2030",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The holiness of Jesus Christ is seen in his divine nature and work, as he stands apart from and above the created world with divine power, authority and purity. Recognition of the holiness of Jesus Christ leads both to a realisation of sin and unworthiness and to worship and adoration.</p>\n<h2>The holy character of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Its divine origin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:35\">LUK 1:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:1-John1:2\">JHN 1:1–1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:31\">JHN 3:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:23\">JHN 8:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:3\">JHN 13:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:14\">JHN 17:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:16\">JHN 17:16</a></p>\n<h3>Its divine nature</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:9\">COL 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:30\">JHN 10:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:38\">JHN 10:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:10\">JHN 14:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:6\">PHP 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>Its divine purity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26\">HEB 7:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:19\">1PE 1:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:22\">1PE 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:3\">1JN 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:5\">1JN 3:5</a></p>\n<h3>Its divine power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:30\">ACT 4:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:38\">ACT 10:38</a></p>\n<h2>The holy work of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>He is set apart as God's servant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:27\">ACT 4:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:31\">JHN 14:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:26\">ACT 3:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:7-Phil2:8\">PHP 2:7–2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:7\">HEB 10:7</a></p>\n<h3>His life is consecrated to the will and purpose of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39\">MAT 26:39</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:35-Mark14:36\">MRK 14:35–14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:42\">MAT 26:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:49-John12:50\">JHN 12:49–12:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:31\">JHN 14:31</a></p>\n<h3>He is appointed as the judge of sinners</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:22\">JHN 5:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:26-John5:27\">JHN 5:26–5:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:31\">ACT 17:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:10\">2CO 5:10</a></p>\n<h3>He makes God's people holy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:12\">HEB 13:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:19\">JHN 17:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:27\">EPH 5:25–5:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:11\">HEB 2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:10\">HEB 10:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:14\">HEB 10:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:4-1Pet2:5\">1PE 2:4–2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:9-1Pet2:10\">1PE 2:9–2:10</a></p>\n<h2>Declarations of the holiness of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p>By David:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:10\">PSA 16:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:27\">ACT 2:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:35\">ACT 13:35</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:24\">MRK 1:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:34\">LUK 4:34</a> <em>by demons</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:35\">LUK 1:35</a> <em>by the angel Gabriel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:69\">JHN 6:69</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:14\">ACT 3:14</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:7\">REV 3:7</a> <em>by Jesus Christ himself</em></p>\n<h2>Results of recognising the holiness of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Awareness of sin and unworthiness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:8\">LUK 5:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:8\">MAT 8:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:6-Luke7:7\">LUK 7:6–7:7</a></p>\n<h3>Fear</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:28-Matt8:34\">MAT 8:28–8:34</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:9-Mark5:17\">MRK 5:9–5:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:26-Luke8:37\">LUK 8:26–8:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:17\">REV 1:17</a></p>\n<h3>Adoration and worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:8-Rev5:14\">REV 5:8–5:14</a></p>",
